.code-graph/

# gstack project artifacts (security reports, plans, telemetry) — local-only, may
# leak attack-path summaries onto a public repo if accidentally git-add'd.
.gstack/

# Claude Code workspace state (sessions, permission grants, local hooks) — user-specific + transient.
.claude/

# docs/ is local-only by default. Tracked + shipped exceptions (functional
# reference docs that adopters / contributors need):
#  - docs/superpowers/ (design + implementation plan)
#  - docs/ADDING-NEW-HOOK.md (external contract: how to add a hook)
#  - docs/RULE-HITS-SCHEMA.md (external contract: JSONL schema)
#  - docs/cross-project-pilot.md (external contract: portability checklist for adopters)
#  - docs/ARCHITECTURE.md (three-layer design + hook taxonomy reference)
#  - docs/HOOK-PROTOCOL.md (hook stdin/stdout I/O contract)
# Historical / analysis scratch stays local: claude-spec-hooks-PLAN.md,
# spec-audit-*.md, and the *.txt review reports.
docs/*
!docs/superpowers/
!docs/ADDING-NEW-HOOK.md
!docs/RULE-HITS-SCHEMA.md
!docs/cross-project-pilot.md
!docs/ARCHITECTURE.md
!docs/HOOK-PROTOCOL.md
